{"id":"nlin/0010001","submitter":"Oleg Zaitsev","authors":"R. E. Prange (1), R. Narevich (2), and Oleg Zaitsev (1) ((1) U. of\n  Maryland, (2) U. of Kentucky)","title":"Quantum Spectra and Wave Functions in Terms of Periodic Orbits for\n  Weakly Chaotic Systems","comments":"9 pages, 8 eps figures","journal-ref":"Physica Scripta T90, 134 (2001).","doi":"10.1238/Physica.Topical.090a00134","report-no":null,"categories":"nlin.CD","license":null,"abstract":"  Special quantum states exist which are quasiclassical quantizations of\nregions of phase space that are weakly chaotic. In a weakly chaotic region, the\norbits are quite regular and remain in the region for some time before escaping\nand manifesting possible chaotic behavior. Such phase space regions are\ncharacterized as being close to periodic orbits of an integrable reference\nsystem. The states are often rather striking, and can be concentrated in\nspatial regions. This leads to possible phenomena. We review some methods we\nhave introduced to characterize such regions and find analytic formulas for the\nspecial states and their energies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 30 Sep 2000 00:14:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-10-31"}
